        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0415.jpg" n="part3_p023.jpg" xml:id="img_0023" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part3_p023.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_23_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>410-
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>all his strength on the full sevelopment of one individual who is supposed to become an outstanding
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>representative of the human possibility in the future society. This is the humanistic education,
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>and many of the great Ihilosopers were teachers in aristocratic houses in which they had to
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>perform this kind of education, and we have aristocrats like Montaigne and Shaftesbury, and others
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>of France and England, who INDEED were representatives, of highest degree, of human potentialities.
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>Now the second is the communication of the Hchnical skills to everybody. Out of this
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_23_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>idea, which develpped a little later than the Renaissance idea, with the Conising democratic
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>ideology, we have the concept of the universal public school—not public school in the sense of
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/> maent Britain, where it simply meant a school in which not only one teacher is in a house to
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>teach the aristocrats, but the sons come together in institutes where you have to beinenc¬
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>a decide before your birth in order to be put in at all! Now this has very little to do with
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>"public"--but in England, you must know that the word "public school" is the highest
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>expression of the most aristocratic form of school. But, like the other counties, they also
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>introduced schools for everybody. And since the 18th century, for instance in Germany,
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>everybody had to go to these schools. Why? What was the idea of THIS education? I myself
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_23_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>went to such a real public school, where we were together with all workers, andifricuitural
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>laborers, and sons of craftsmen and small traders, etc., in a little town. What you first of all
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>also
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>and
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>iuam are technical skills: reading and writing, beyond this, later on, not school which bring
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>as labor or lower middle class people.
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>you never to some of your later jobs,
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>But it was not only this. The school was also used in order to give some of the goods
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>of culture. From the very beginning, an element of introduced in these school,
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>for instance introduction into nature, the surincunding nature; an'introduction into the national
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>cʼest lʼobligation dʼautre beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>dʼaprès
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>dans les
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>de mon frere,
               <lb facs="#facs_23_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>dʼune manière
            </p>
            
